# GU Package

This package is a tiny reusable storage helper for:
- a .env file with GitHub token, username, and repo name
- a dbs.json file for database names
- a batch wrapper for syncing from any project

## Quick usage

From the project folder:

```bat
sync.bat token set YOUR_TOKEN
sync.bat name set YOUR_NAME
sync.bat repo set YOUR_REPO
sync.bat db create users
sync.bat db update users email=demo@example.com
sync.bat db get users
sync.bat sync
```

## Behavior

- The package checks the configured repo name first.
- If the repo directory is full, it creates the next repo bucket like repo-name-1, repo-name-2, and so on.
- Each DB is split into JSON chunks.
- A chunk is reused while it still fits under the configured size limit.
- When a chunk would exceed the limit, a new chunk is created.
- Reading a DB merges all matching chunks into one view.
